      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A very low inventory turnover ratio means you are holding onto unsold stock, which often leads to significant capital being tied up in items that might never sell again. This surplus takes up valuable retail space and increases your storage costs, compounding the financial risk that continuously purchasing new stock could deplete your cash reserves before those older items are sold. For a boutique, failing to move slow-moving fashion quickly is a direct threat to your profitability and can render your entire quarterly performance unprofitable even with high sales volume.",
      "source": "target",
