      "content": "You can distinguish a temporary dip from a structural hoarding problem by analyzing if recent purchases significantly exceeded sales revenue over the last few months. Another telling sign is comparing your current 'days sales of inventory'—how long it takes to sell a year's worth of goods—against your historical average or industry benchmarks to see if the stagnation is sudden or chronic. If your gross profit margins are high and you aren't clearing stock despite promotions, it usually points to an over-ordering issue rather than a fleeting market trend.",
